width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> 8D1</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#FF9300>(5/28/03 8:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/findygmagbodycarclubfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   More questions</span><hr size=1> G-body, G-body, G-body, G-body.........got it now!  Thanks for the heads up!<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   From what vehicles could I get the motor mounts and springs from?  Will the motor mounts and springs from any other GM G-body from that era (78-87) work?  There seems to be alot of V8 Cutlasses around here in the boneyards.  Do I need to change the trans crossmember?  Will the driveshaft need to be swapped out also?  I will probably have to live with the V6 for a little bit, are there any tricks to getting the old 3.8 running smooth.  Until I swap in the smallblock, I'm really not concerned with performance.  The V6 is running a little rough right now (which is why the price is so low).  Any more help you could send me is greatly appreciated. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F9FBFD><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bindygmagbodycarclub.showUserPublicProfile?gid=indyagbody>Indy AG Body</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>ezOP</span><br>  Posts: 18<br> <font color=#FF9300>(5/30/03 11:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/findygmagbodycarclubfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   'Bu</span><hr size=1> Well, the motor mounts can come out of any bodystyle 78-83 Malibu, or any 78-88 Monte Carlo.  Those are the only motor mounts you'd want to use simply because they are Chevy small block motor mounts, not Olds, Buick, or Pontiac.  The BOP's tend to be a bit different, and won't always work.  As far as the springs go, any G-body with a stock V8 will work.  Those are all the same across the board.  The tranny crossmember will work fine, as long as you stay with a TH-350 or TH-400.  They are pretty much all the same exact design, with a few differences.  Pretty much the only differences between the Th-200, 250, 350, and 400 is that the higher the number, the stronger the tranny is.  The driveshaft will work, but you'll probably want to put new U-joints in just to be on the safe side.  As far as that 3.8 goes, you could always turbo it like the Grand Nationals.  Not really, but that would be kick @ss!  Is the 3.8 carbeureted or F.I?  There are different tweaks for each.  Let me know.  Hope this helps. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub98.ezboard.com/findygmagbodycarclubfrm2.showPrevMessage?topicID=25.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub98.ezboard.com/findygmagbodycarclubfrm2.showNextMessage?topicID=25.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/findygmagbodycarclubfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25.topic&index=3><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/prefabs/ez/addreply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/findygmagbodycarclubfrm2.emailToFriend?topicID=25.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/findygmagbodycarclubfrm2.threadControl?topicID=25.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/posticons/techops.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a h